@translation labeled en project

@(1) Speak to my king, @lab{2}saying (the words of) Aradmu, your servant: 

@(3 = 9) You commanded me @lab{3}to undertake an expedition to Subir, @lab{4}to secure the taxes on the frontier territory, @lab{5}to inform (them) about (your) orders, @lab{6–7}to confer (with the elites of Subir) about Apilaša, the high commissioner, and have them come to agreement, @lab{8}@i{so that he could bring to them (i.e. the Subir elites) up-to-date instructions}.^2^

@note ^2^  Alternative translation: so that as part of the daily instructions he could bring them (the people of Subir) good news.

@(10 - 18)  @i{Drop (chasing) winds in the desert and robbers in the fields}!^3^ @lab{11}Until you have reached Apilaša, my high commissioner, @lab{12}@i{ignore all of this so that you can ... your face before him (without delay)},” {-13 }so that their (local) dignitaries learn their orders, @lab{14}so that your battle cries should cover the land(s). @lab{15}... @lab{16}staked poles/lances inlaid with silver, carnelian, and lapis ... @lab{17}nir-stone, gold, carnelian, lapis, ... @lab{18}Choice guards, five hundred strong, (stood to) his right and left ...

@note ^3^  Alternative translation: make winds and robbers disappear from the desert!
