@translation labeled en project
@(1) Speak to Aradmu, @lab{2}saying (the words) of Šulgi, your king: 

@(3) (Apilaša), the one I sent you to—is he not your own trusted subordinate? @lab{4}Did he not receive (his) orders from your very own hands? @lab{5}What is more, how could you so misunderstand the true meaning of all that he has been doing? 

@(6) As far as I am concerned, you were to make the frontier territory secure as my representative, @lab{7}to organize the people and keep them obedient, @lab{8}and once you reached the cities of the frontier, to discern their attitudes @lab{9}and to learn what their dignitaries are saying, @lab{10}so that my battle cry would fill the mountains, @lab{11}my mighty battle weapons fall upon the foreign lands, @lab{12}and my “storm” cover over the homeland! @lab{13}“@i{Drop (chasing) winds in the desert and robbers in the fields}!^2^ @lab{14}Until you have reached Apilaša, my high commissioner, @lab{15}@i{ignore all of this so that you can ... your face before him (without delay)}!” @lab{16}Thus did I command you!^3^

#note: ^2^  Alt. transl.: make winds and robbers disappear from the desert!

#note: ^3^  Two texts have an additional line 16a; see commentary.


@(17) If my high commissioner had not expanded (his powers), just as I would have,^4^ @lab{18}if he had not sat on a throne on a dais placed over a fine carpet,^5^ @lab{19}had not set his feet on a golden footstool, @lab{22}had not by his very own authority appointed and removed @lab{20}governors from the office of governor, @lab{21}office holders from official positions, @lab{23}had not (punished anyone) by death or blinding, @lab{24}(and) had not promoted those of his own choosing over others—@lab{25}how else could he have secured the frontier? @lab{26}If you (truly) love me @lab{27}then you will not be so set against him! 

#note: ^4^  Var.: If you had not had not expanded my high commissioner’s powers as my representative. 

#note: ^5^  Alt. transl.: under an awning.


@(28) It is you who have expanded your powers so that you no longer understand your (own) guardsmen! @lab{29}He has made you learn (the hard way) the responsibilities of those people, as well as the responsibilities of his own warriors! 

@(30 - 34) If you are indeed both my most faithful retainers,^6^ @lab{31}(you will listen together while) they read out this tablet before the two of you.^7^ @lab{32}Both of you must come to an agreement @lab{33}and secure the foundation-s of the frontier territory! @lab{34}It is urgent!

#note: ^6^  Var.: If you (sing.) are indeed my faithful retainer...

#note: ^7^  Viz.: have them read out aloud my inscribed tablet before your (pl.) very own eyes.
&Q000541 = 3. Aradmu to Šulgi 2 (ArŠ 2, 3.1.3 + 3.1.11. A2a, RCU 3+4) 
@composite
#project: cku
#atf: use unicode
