#lem: namgur[thickness]; erin[people]; niŋ[thing]; dug[speak]

19. 	ki-saŋ-ŋál-la igi-zu-šè {ŋiš}gu-za-àm ha-ra-ab-dúr-dè-en
#lem: kisaŋŋala[stronghold]; igi[eye]; guza[chair]; durun[sit]

## not ha-ra-ab-durun-ne-en ?
20. 	a-ma-ru-kam
#lem: amaru[flood]

@translation labeled en project
@(1) Speak to Aradmu, @lab{2}saying (the words) of Šulgi, your king: 

@(3) When Abaindasa, captain of the armed forces, @lab{4}sent that letter (to me/you) @lab{5}... important... so that he @i{could} @i{confirm} the punishment that you imposed on him. @lab{6}Why did you remove him from that regiment @lab{7}and throw him in prison? @lab{8}Having reduced the punishment that you had imposed by your own volition, @lab{9}now that the enemy is coming against you, reinstate him into that regiment! 

@(10) [@i{By the order of}] Ur-Namma, the father who begot me, @lab{11}... fortress ... @lab{12}...I/ you establish/appoint... @lab{13}...fortress ... @lab{14}As soon as my letter concerning him has been sent, @lab{15}reinstate him into that regiment! @lab{16}... @lab{17}You must not diminish (the importance) of that city: @lab{18}its importance to that regiment is something that has (already) has been explained to you, @lab{19}so you should install him in a stronghold before you as if on a throne! @lab{20}It is urgent!

