@translation labeled en project
@(1) Speak to my king, @lab{2}saying (the words) of Aradmu, your servant:

@(3) (Concerning the matter of) Abaindasa, captain of the royal armed forces, that my king sent me (a message) about; @lab{4}my king must be informed about the matter. 

@(5) When I focused my attention on Zimudar, @lab{6}I was in the process of mustering troops for my king’s military service,^1^ @lab{7}but when Abaindasa inspected those troops, @lab{8}2000 of those men were missing. @lab{9}He had not gone to..., nor had he returned. @lab{10}He had abandoned the fortress, @i{o my king}, @i{and then (re)captured (it)!} @lab{11}That crime was a very serious crime against my king! @lab{12–13}...

#note: ^1^  Alt. transl.: my king’s expedition.


@(14) Whatever you, my king order me to do, (I will do)! @lab{15}Now my king is informed (about all of this)! 


