$ (Colophon D)
@translation labeled en project
@(1) Speak to my king, @lab{2}saying (the words) of Aradmu, your servant:

@(3) When my king dispatched me to ... the task, @lab{4}once I approached those troops, @lab{5}the generals, lieutenants, and captains of my king’s far-flung troops @lab{6}inquired about the health of my king; @lab{7}and shouted out ‘Long Live the King!’” @lab{8}When I was close to the work(-site), @lab{9}after I inspected the work that my king had sent me to, @lab{10}the one guilty of a capital offence was handed over for execution, @lab{11}the sentenced had to bear their punishment. @lab{12}The one who doubled his work-(load) was very well paid, @lab{13}his wages were paid out in silver for each day. 

@(14) Abaindasa, the captain of the royal armed forces, @lab{15}who had been returned to the ranks by my king, @lab{16}abandoned the task (assigned by) my king and rushed to work building fortifications. @lab{17}My king, because the orders were not being ... @lab{18}Šulgi-x dispatched? a messenger, ...@lab{19}but because he rebelled ... but could not send my messenger @lab{20}... @lab{21}He destroyed/broke ... and had to bear punishment @lab{22}and was ousted from that troop. @lab{23}That crime was a very serious crime against my king! @lab{24}After he was entrusted to a second man @lab{25}(that man) carried out the punishment. 

@(26) Whatever my king orders me, I will do. @lab{27}My king should know (about all this). @lab{28}From this very [day] on, I will never neglect my king’s orders! @lab{29}My kings [orders?] must never be transgressed!


