#lem: lugal[king]; zu[know]

@translation labeled en project
@(1) Speak to my king, @lab{2}saying (the words) of Aradmu, your servant:

@(3) My king, your pronouncements are as the pronouncements of An, which cannot be changed. @lab{4}Your destiny has been bestowed to you as to a god! @lab{5}And as for the fortifications that my king commissioned me to finish, I have restored the work to its previous condition. @lab{6}(As a result) the enemy’s access to the frontier territory has been blocked. @lab{7–8}My king’s name supreme illuminates (everything) from North to South, from East to West, to the borders of the entire homeland. @lab{9}The enemy Amorites.... @lab{10}Kurgamabi (Akk.: Kunši-matum) to Šulgi ... the fortress Igihursaŋa ... @lab{11}And Abaindasa ...

@(12) The tablet(s) that my king ... @lab{13}Whatever you, my king or[der me to do, (I will do)].

@(14) Now my king [is informed] (about all of this)! 


