@translation labeled en project
@(1) Speak to my king, @lab{2}saying (the words) of Aradmu, your servant:

@(3) Your Majesty, the far-flung territories that have been given to you to rule—@lab{4}they are obedient, and of one mind. @lab{5–6}You are the rightful shepherd of Šulgi’s people, numerous as blades of grass, @lab{6}the god of mortals/the population, of the lower and the upper (lands), @lab{7}@i{they look to you (with reverence)} ! @lab{8}The far-flung peoples, numerous as blades of grass, from the mighty waters of the Tigris and Euphrates,{-9 }... of the Tigris, that my lord has @i{entrusted to me}, ...

@(5’) ... citizens? of the land of Gutium, @lab{6’}... Mari? and Rapiqum, @lab{7’}who have ... are before me. @lab{8}Whatever you, my king, order me to do, I will do.


