@translation labeled en project
@(1) Speak to my king, @lab{2}saying (the words) of Ur-dun, commercial agent, your servant: 

@(3) My king gave me capital @lab{4–5}and dispatched me to a distant foreign land to purchase juniper resin. @lab{6}But once I had entered the foreign land @lab{7}and purchased the resin, @lab{8}Apilaša, the royal commissioner, was very firm with me, and @lab{9}they appropriated my purchases. @lab{10}When I stood at the gate of his (local) palace, @lab{11}no one wanted to investigate my complaint.

@(12) And as for Aradmu, your servant, and Babati, the high commissioner, @lab{14}they had gone @lab{13}from Zimudar to Simurum, @lab{15}@i{and to inform them}..., @lab{16}[they have sent] their messengers. @lab{17}My king-.... @lab{18}This confiscation cannot be undone without using force. @lab{19}O king, (my messenger) has given you my accounting (of the matter). @lab{20}Whatever you, my king, order me to do, (I will do).


