#note: ^2^  34a (N4 only): ⸢a⸣-ma-ru-k[am].
@translation labeled en project
@(1) Speak to my king, @lab{2}saying (the words) of Puzur-Šulgi,^3^ general of Bad-Igihursaŋa, your servant:

#note: ^3^  Var.: Puzur-Numušda, Puzur-Marduk.

@(4 = 5) Is it not for the sake of his own well-being @lab{4}that my king fashions (objects) of silver and gold for the gods? @lab{6}My king, for the well-being of the army and of his homeland, @lab{7 - 8}has built the great fortifications of Igihursaŋa for the sake of the vile enemy and of the people of his homeland. 

@(9) But now the (enemy?) troops have mustered (for battle). @lab{10}A certain individual who was brought before me as a deserter @lab{11}gave me some information as he was passing (through) and then went back out (again). @lab{12}Now I really know the enemy’s passwords! 

@(13) The enemy has concentrated (all) his forces for battle but my forces are insufficient (to keep them off). @lab{14}It is impossible to strengthen the fortifications against him, nor (properly) guard it. @lab{15}In the sector under the responsibility of Puzur-Numušda,^4^ governor of Ullum-ṣeḫrum, @lab{16}a 300 m. section @i{had sagged} and collapsed in the middle; @lab{17}in the sector under the responsibility of Lugal-melam, the overseer of the Šeššektum canal, @lab{18}30 m. of his section can be breached; @lab{19}in the sector under the responsibility of Kakugani,^5^ governor of the inland territory, @lab{20}a 210 m. section, its face and based are badly damaged, @lab{21}(and) in the part under the responsibility of Takil-ilišu, canal inspector of the Abgal and Me-Enlila waterways, @lab{22}240 m. of his section @i{does not have its perimeter laid out yet}. @lab{23}Although I cannot know ahead of time when the enemy will advance against (the fortifications), @lab{24}(it is evident) that the enemy has concentrated (all) his forces for battle, @lab{25}and his troops are encamped in the mountain valleys. 

#note: ^4^  Var.: Šu-Marduk, Šu-Nunu, Šu-Numušda.

#note: ^5^  Var.: Šu-Numušda.

@(26) If my king is agreeable, @lab{27}he will raise for me a very large contingent (viz. 7200) of workers and send them here immediately. @lab{-28 - 29}Seventy @i{Sudalunutum} troopers should also come here to me. @lab{-30}I am resolved, and so I shall dislodge them (i.e., the enemy), @lab{31}so let this be known, for his (the enemy’s) sins have been grievous from (primeval) night to the end of days! @lab{32}(Be assured), I am the true servant of my lord Šulgi,^6^ @lab{33}and I will definitely finish (this work)! @lab{34}Now my king is informed (about all of this)!^7^

#note: ^6^  One text adds: @lab{32a}My letter, it will not be neglected, will it?

#note: ^7^  One text adds: @lab{34a}It is urgent!


