$ (Colophon J (X2))
@translation labeled en project
@(1 - 2) Speak to Puzur-Šulgi, general of Bad-Igihursaŋa, @lab{3}saying (the words of) Šulgi, your king:

@(4) When I had constructed Bad-Igihursaŋa, @lab{5 - 6}An and Enlil gave me to rule all the lands and far-flung peoples. @lab{7}And as for me... @lab{8}the cities of the homeland, province by province, @lab{9}as well as the peoples of the far-flung homeland rested in safe pastures. @lab{10}[@i{I made them dwell}] in far-flung places @i{and peaceful habitations.} @lab{11}... dwelling(s) ...

@(12 - 13) Have the governor(s) and the prefect(s) [@i{bring their men}] and mobilize all their cities, @lab{14}and have someone take charge@i{ of the beginning} of the work; @lab{15}wherever the fortification has deteriorated, it must be restored, @lab{16}torn down, and then rebuilt, @lab{17}and @i{(the repairs to) the fallen sides (of the wall)} must be finished in the course of one month! @lab{18}You/I will then ask him ([Aradmu?] for a report) about this work.

@(19) And now the the Tidnumites have returned to (help) me from the highlands. @lab{20}(Moreover), Lu-Nanna, governor of Zimudar province, @lab{21}@i{is coming to you} with his worker troops. @lab{22}He will have his own [travel provision]s for you, @lab{23}@i{...}

@(1’) ... @lab{2’}... dispatch ... @lab{3’}[@i{When the work/fortifications}] are finished,-@lab{4’}then, after Lu-Nanna, the governor of Zimudar @lab{5’}has left both of you with his worker troops, @lab{6’}you and Aradmu must not cease supervising/@i{alter your assignment}, @lab{7’}and you must not neglect the important orders @i{that are in your hands}. @lab{8’}The work must progress day and night; @lab{9’}neither of you is to sleep by night or day—you must both know about this! @lab{10’}It is urgent!


