@translation labeled en project
@(1)  Speak to Puzur-Šulgi, general of Bad-Igihursaŋa, @lab{2}saying (the words of) Šulgi, your king: 

@(3) When the great fortifications of Bad-Igihursaŋa were being built @lab{4}so that the Amorites could not descend on the homeland, @lab{5}nor water (their herds) at the banks of the Abgal as well as the Tigris and Euphrates, @lab{6}that [the people of the far-flung homeland] rest in sa[fe pastures], @lab{7}and not be terrori[zed in their dwellings], @lab{8}to bring ...@lab{9}to go on the roads ...@lab{10 - 13}... @lab{14}let them mobilize [all their villages, one by one] @lab{15}and appoint [the man in charge of the construction]. @lab{16}[The fortifications must be torn down], and then rebuilt. @lab{17}... send me swiftly... 

@(18) After I consult you about this undertaking,@lab{19 - 20}Lu-Nanna, governor of Zimudar province is to come to you with his worker troops. @lab{21 - 25}...@lab{26}You (sing.) [should not allow the worker troops] to leave. @lab{27}... @lab{28}neither/both of you is to [...!] @lab{29}It is [ur]gent! 


