@translation labeled en project
@h1 Sumerian

@(1) Speak to Išbi-Erra, @sup(${2}$) saying (the words of) Šulgi, your king:

@(3) You make me very happy with the news that you sent me. @sup(${4}$) Who could give me a house-born slave as reliable as you? @sup(${5}$) Who has someone so able entrusted to his lord? @sup(${6}$) Now, concerning all that you have written to me, @sup(${7}$) I am sending you a tablet with the secret instructions.^2^ 

#note: ^2^  Or: passwords.

@(8) Babati, the high commissioner, who is (like) a grandfather to me, @sup(${9}$) the judicious elder, skilled in council, @sup(${10}$)has now arrived before you (with) six hundred talents of silver and six hundred talents of gold. @lab{11 - 12}... @sup(${13}$) I have (also) sent you news about the troops: forward them to him @sup(${14}$) and (do) whatever he asks. @sup(${15}$) Please be careful that his heart does not turn (against you)! @sup(${16}$) And as for you, take the gold and silver from his care, @sup(${17}$) and buy all the grain at the prevailing market rate. @sup(${18}$) @i{Once it is all in your possession, you do not have to hurry}. 

@(19) From this day on you are the son who gladdens my heart. @sup(${20}$) You are established (as the guardian) against all of Amurru and Elam; sit as my representative! @sup(${21}$) Sit before them on a throne (set up on) a gold (encrusted) dais, @sup(${22}$) so that you will be the one before whom their envoys prostrate themselves. @sup(${23}$) Elevate yourself over them, never turn back! @sup(${24}$) Depose governors, appoint governors, @sup(${25}$) appoint generals, assign lieutenants, @sup(${26}$) @i{punish the guilty by blinding}. 

@(27) As for a soldier who finds favor with you, @sup(${28}$) build for him his (first) adult house---your favor will be great. @sup(${29}$) Now, concerning all that I have written to you, @sup(${30}$) it is urgent, you must not change your allegiance!

@translation labeled en Akkadian
@h1 Akkadian

@(1) <Speak to Išbi-Erra: @sup(${2}$) thus says Šulgi, your king:> 

@(3) I greatly rejoiced at the news that you sent me. @sup(${4}$) Who could give me a servant who is as reliable as you? @sup(${5}$) Who has one so able who is so exceedingly pleasing to his lord? @sup(${6}$) Now, concerning all that you have written to me, @sup(${7}$) I respond to you without delay. 

@(8 - 10) I have now sent to you Babati, the high commissioner, @sup(${9}$) the judicious elder, who is skilled in council, (together with) six hundred talents of silver and sixty talents of gold; @lab{11 - 12}@i{he has come to you in the matter of the credit balance left over from what the troops have already received}. @sup(${13}$) News of my troops have been sent to you: @sup(${14}$) forward them to him and do whatever he asks. @sup(${15}$) Please be careful that his heart does not turn against you! 

@(16 - 17) And as for you, take the gold and silver from his hand and buy up the all grain at the prevailing market rate, @sup(${18}$) and should anyone claim it from you, you should pay it no mind.

@(19) From this day on, you are the son who gladdens my heart. @sup(${20}$) You are established (as the guardian) against all of Amurru and Elam; sit as my representative! @sup(${21}$) You sit before them on a throne (set up on) a gold (encrusted) dais, @sup(${22}$) so that you will be the one before whom their envoys prostrate themselves. @sup(${23}$) Elevate yourself over them, so that you never turn back! @sup(${24}$) Depose governors, appoint governors, @sup(${25}$) appoint generals, assign lieutenants! @sup(${26}$) Keep a check on transgressors, @i{rip off} the ears of (guilty) people!

@(27) As for a soldier who finds favor with you, @sup(${28}$) build for him his (first) adult house so that he will return your favor. @sup(${29}$) Now, concerning all that you have written to me, @sup(${30}$) it is urgent, do not change your allegiance!

&Q000551 = 16. Amar-Sin to Šulgi 1 (AmŠ1, 3.1.12)
