@translation labeled en project
@(1) Speak to my king, @lab{2}saying (the words) of Amar-Sin, your servant: 

@(3) In the matter of the field that my liege spoke to me about: @lab{4}... diminished. @lab{5}Because I am my king’s servant, @i{as soon as I saw his majesty’s face, I dropped my weapons (to deal with the issue)}. @lab{6}I (?) dispatched (someone) to the field in the territory. @lab{7}@i{In the plans, the riverbank did not ... the field; it’s side seems much too short for me}. @lab{8}That field does not (even) come close to the river by forty (fifty) km. @lab{9}The irrigation ditch does not wind around the Hursag. @lab{10}There is no deceit here; (I am obedient) to the orders that my liege has given. @lab{11}That field cannot be lost (to cultivation)! @lab{12}Whatever you, my king order me to do, (I will do) ... Now my king knows (all this)!


