#note: ^1^  Var.: u₄ kur-kur-ra hé-en-dul.
@translation labeled en project
@(1) Speak to Šu-Sin, my king: @lab{2}saying (the words of) Šarrum-bani, royal commissioner, your servant:

@(3) You commissioned me to carry out construction on the great fortifications of Muriq-Tidnim @lab{4}and presented your views to me as follows: “The Amorites have repeatedly raided the frontier territory.” @lab{7}You commanded me @lab{5}to rebuild the fortifications, to cut off their access, @lab{6 - 7}and thus to prevent them from repeatedly overwhelming the fields through a breach (in the defenses) between theTigris and Euphrates. 

@(8) As I was leaving (for the assignment), @lab{9}from the banks of the Abgal canal up thought to the territory of Zimudar, @lab{10}I levied workers there.

## thought -> through

@(11) When I had been working on the fortifications that then measured 26 dana (269 km.), @lab{12}after having reached (the area) between the two mountain ranges, @lab{13}the Amorite camped in the mountains turned his attention to my building activities. @lab{14}(The leader of) Simurum came to his aid, and @lab{15}he went out against me between the mountain ranges of Ebih to do battle. @lab{16}And therefore I, even thought I could not @i{spare} corvée workers (for fighting), @lab{17}went out to confront him in battle.

## thought -> though

@(18) If my king is agreeable, @lab{19}he will reinforce my laborers @i{so that I can get to work}. @lab{20}Although I have not been able to reach @i{the (main) fortification tower} of the frontier territory, [as soon as I received] information, @lab{21}I sent an envoy @i{to the interior}. @lab{22}But the territory has changed its allegiance, @lab{23}and so I have not neglected to build the fortifications— (to the contrary), I have been building and fighting (at the same time). @lab{24 - 25}@i{Even if (another) royal commissioner were to be selected from the grandest of (military) units},@i{ he would still not be able to attain the goal of preventing the frontier territory from changing its allegiance}.

@(26) After I dispatched my envoy to you, @lab{27 - 28}right behind him I dispatched (another) envoy to Lu-Nanna, the governor of Zimudar, and @lab{29}he sent me a very large contingent (viz. 7200) of workers. @lab{30}There are enough corvée laborers but not enough fighting men! @lab{31}Once my king gives the orders to release the workers (for military duty), @lab{32}then when (the enemy) raids, I shall be able to fight him!

@(33) He (Lu-Nanna?) dispatched the (same) man to the nobles of your frontier territory @lab{34}and they presented their case to me as follows: @lab{35}“We cannot even guard all the cities by ourselves, @lab{36}how can (we) give you (more) troops?” @lab{37}They then sent my messenger back (to me) though him.

@(38) Ever since my king commanded me, {39}day and night I have been diligently doing the assigned work as well as fighting (the enemy). {40 }Because I am obedient to my king’s command (to build the fortifications) and I continue to @i{battle again and again}, {41 }even though the requisite force has not been assigned to me, I will not cease fighting. {42} Now my king is informed (about all of this)!^2^

#note: ^2^  Var: May the storm (of my king) cover the land!



