@translation labeled en project
@(1) Speak to Šarrum-bani: @lab{2}saying (the words of) Šu-Sin, your king:

@(3) The envoy whom I sent to you, ... above and beyond ... @lab{4}At daybreak my orders that I had provided, to me ... you were not to exceed. @lab{5}After you went away, before ... @lab{6}As for me, whatever (you) say to me ... @lab{7}After you set out for to the center of the frontier territory, @lab{8}you approached the territory and after spending the night ... @lab{9}Its nobles ... @lab{10}If by yourself ... @lab{11}their understanding ... his ... @lab{12}Their nobles then staged an ambush against you. @lab{13}When their @i{people had been expelled}, @lab{14}like them the frontier territory ... @lab{15}If their officer ... @lab{16}are of one mind, @lab{17}you will not be able to root them out from their hiding places. @lab{18}The enemy all gathered together ... @lab{19}When their cities have been handed over, @lab{20}until they come out from these fortifications, let no one get through. @lab{21}Once their (fighting) men had been killed, @lab{22}their women/workers of the citi(es) of your territory, who had been captured, were not to be [harmed?]. @lab{23}Thus did I command you. @lab{24}Why did you not act in accordance with my instructions? 


@(25 - 26) But although it was not (normally) in your power to execute and blind people, nor to destroy cities, @lab{27}I gave you (that) authority. @lab{28}When earlier <my> father Šulgi had built @i{Bad-igihursaga}, @lab{29}none of you were there. @lab{30}The throne is mine, it not the throne of Šulgi! @lab{31}Lu-Nanna,^4^ the governor of Zimudar @lab{32}is to come to you and @lab{33}he will bring 60 @i{soldiers}. @lab{34}He is to send them [from among his own conscripts]. @lab{35}Babati, the high commissioner, @i{in accordance with orders} @lab{36}that I have already given to him, is to build the fortifications. @lab{37 - 38}But you, with the workers that have been entrusted to you—dig the moat! @lab{40}You were both enjoined @lab{39}to do nothing that would alter the allegiance of the frontier territory; @lab{41}until (that) territory is secured, @lab{42}neither you can demobilize the troops! @lab{43 - 44}Then, have envoys bring news of the territory to me each morning! @lab{45}It is urgent!

#note: ^4^  Written as {m}<{ }lú>-{d}en-ki.
