@translation labeled en project
@h1 Part A

@(1) Speak to Ibbi-Sin, my king, @lab{2}saying (the words of) Išbi-Erra, your servant:

@(3 - 4) You gave me orders concerning an expedition from Isin to Kazallu to purchase grain. @lab{5}As the market price of grain was equivalent to (one shekel) per liter, @lab{6}twenty talents of silver was invested in the purchase of grain. @lab{7}Word having reached me that hostile Amorites had entered your frontier territory, @lab{8}I proceeded to deliver all the grain—72,000 kor—into (the city of) Isin. @lab{9}But now all the Amorites have entered the homeland, @lab{10}and have captured all the great storehouses, one by one. @lab{11}Because of (these) Amorites I cannot hand over the grain for threshing;^5^ @lab{12}they are too strong for me, and I am made to stay put. @lab{13}Therefore, my king should (order) the caulking of 600 barges of 120 liter capacity, @lab{14}@i{escorted by 12 armed ships}, and load each with 20 @i{swords}, 30 @i{bows}, @lab{15}load each ship with 30 @i{beams} and five (additional) hatches, and have all the boats ... @lab{16 - 17}so that they can be brought down by water, through the Idkura and the Palištum canals so they can pile up (the grain) in stacks (for drying), @lab{18}and I will myself go out to meet him (i.e., Ibbi-Sin). 

#note: ^5^  Followed by two fragmentary lines in X1.


@(19) I shall take responsibility for the place where the boat(s) moor, {-20 }so that the 72,000 kor of grain—that is all of the grain—will be placed (there), and be safe. @lab{21 - 22}Should there be a shortage of grain, I will be the one who brings you grain.^6^

#note: ^6^  Var.: Should you lack grain, I will bring you that grain.


@(23) My king is troubled by the war with the Elamite, @lab{24}but his own grain rations are rapidly being depleted, @lab{25}so do not release your grip on power, @lab{26}do not rush to become his servant, @lab{27}and to follow him! @lab{28}There is (enough) grain in my city to provision your palace and all the people for fifteen years,^7^ @lab{29}so let the responsibility of guarding the cities of Isin and Nippur be mine!^8^ @lab{30}Now my king is informed (about all of this)! 

#note: ^7^  Var.: I have at my disposal (enough) grain (to provision) your palace and all of its/your cities for fifteen years.

#note: ^8^  Var.: Please let me guard Isin and Nippur for you, let me have (that) responsibility (o my king)!


@h1 Part B

@(31) My king, I am neither afraid, nor worried, and (if I were you) I would certainly not be @i{worried} in there (i.e., Ur). @lab{32}Seek out the intentions of the various gods and attend to them @lab{33 - 34}so that its far-flung people and its supreme populace will be safe and truly@i{ multiply}! 

@(35) Ur, city of wisdom, linking the heavens and the earth; @lab{36}having been built by Great Prince (Enki), the exorcist, (it is a city) whose façade is precious (to the people), @lab{37}one endowed with cosmic rites, whose foundations and ground plans are secure (among all the) lands, south to north, @lab{38}@i{it will surely be spared and its (favorable divine) decision announced!} 

@(39) (Temple) Ekišnuŋal, shrine that envelops the heavens and the earth, without rival—{40 }the Elamite, an evil^9^ vicious dog, {41 }will not defile it, nor render asunder its guardian deities! {42 }@i{My king, all the loudest noisemakers have run away.} 

#note: ^9^  Alt. transl.: destructive.

@(43) Ibbi-Sin, beloved by the gods as he came out of the womb—@lab{44}An, Enlil, and Enki, looked so favorably upon him! @lab{45}Established ... so that its front be secure, @lab{46}are ordering that the doors of the gate of Ur be opened, @lab{47}saying “Who is really king?” @lab{48}But it is you who are the king to whom Enlil gave no rival! @lab{49}So do not ..., so be of good spirits! @lab{50}@i{(He/they) has/have taken revenge}, and secured its foundations for you. @lab{51}Not being ... may your spirit be happy! @lab{52}As long as my king is alive, he will exercise kingship over Ur, @lab{53}and (I will do) whatever my king might command me to do! @lab{54}Please, I will not neglect (your orders)! @lab{55}By Utu, I will not change my allegiance!


