$ (Colophon P (X1))
@translation labeled en project
@(1 - 2) Speak to Puzur-Šulgi, governor of Kazallu, @lab{4}saying (the words of) @lab{3}Ibbi-Sin, your king: 

@(3) Ever since I selected you out of the ranks and made you the governor of Kazallu, @lab{4}have you not been honored throughout the homeland as my representative? @lab{5}Kazallu ... @lab{6}A man who is ...@lab{7}Enlil has not ...from your frontier area. @lab{8}Someone excellent, a man who is like you ... the responsibilities over the smaller cities ... @lab{9}Why is it that all valor has been torn from your heart, @lab{10}why are you so panicked and full of contempt? @lab{11}You even sent someone to me (saying) thus:^4^ @lab{12}“Išbi-Erra has presented his matter before me, @lab{13}and as far as I am concerned, when he finally strikes, I will have to flee!” @lab{14}How is it that you do not know how to repulse Išbi-Erra to his own country? @lab{15 - 16}Why did you and Ŋirbubu, governor of Ŋirkal, not stand up against him with the troops that are under your authority (while you still had the chance)? @lab{17}To restore the lands to their previous condition—that was the assignment you were both given!

#note: ^4^  Var.: But you sent me someone with the following message.

@(18) Enlil had earlier already come to hate Sumer, @lab{19}appointing a monkey descending from its mountain (home) to the stewardship of the homeland. @lab{20 - 21}But now Enlil has handed kingship to a (mere) @i{peddler of exotic spices}, one who chases the wind, to Išbi-Erra, who is not even of Sumerian descent. @lab{22}Moreover, once the assembly of the gods, (decided) to scatter the (inhabitants of the) Sumer, @lab{23}Father Enlil, having conveyed his commands, proceeded to overthrow the homeland. @lab{24}“As long as Ur @i{is imbued with evildoers}, @lab{25}Išbi-Erra, the man of Mari, will tear out its foundations, @lab{26}and Sumer will be measured out,” thus he spoke! @lab{27}And if the governors of the individual cities should gather together, @lab{28}by Enlil’s command Išbi-Erra will fall. 

@(29) But even supposing that he is not (betrayed) as if being handed over to an enemy city by a comrade, @lab{30}and you, although acting as if you were my trusted servant, recognize Išbi-Erra by yourself/out of fear, @lab{31}your statements would do nothing to upset me, @lab{32}for you know very well that I am (a favorite) of the gods.

@(33) Father Enlil, by means of his angry commands, has overthrown the homeland. @lab{34}Come now, he has returned to my side! @lab{35}@i{My complaints were submitted by humble prayer}, @lab{36}and Great Lord Enlil heard me out; @lab{37}he cast his favorable glance upon me, @lab{38}set his holy heart on mercy, @lab{39}and established for me my favorable omen. @lab{40}And after I had the follow-up reading made concerning his @i{pars familiaris} and my @i{pars hostilis},^5^ @lab{41}the weapon-mark on my right side, its trunk is straight, and that (good news) gave me joy; @lab{42}on the weapon-mark on his (i.e., Išbi-Erra’s) left side a filament is suspended,^6^ it is placed (against) the other side. @lab{43}(The message was:) “My enemy shall fall into my hands, he shall be killed, @lab{44}the people, having come out of darkness into the light, will lie in peaceful habitations.” @lab{45}Utu, lord who makes the decisions of the heavens and the earth, has provided (this) omen. 

#note: ^5^  So X1; X2 omits 41 and 42: After I had the follow-up reading made concerning the left and right sides, (the message was): ... 

#note: ^6^  Alt. tr.: is attached.

@(46) Return to reconciliation @i{as before}, @lab{47}come now, (you too) must return to reconciliation, @i{so that all treachery is undone}, @lab{48}so that your can people can work on their harvest. @lab{49}You must not hurry to come to me; @lab{50}(I assure you that) he will not conquer the city that he (wants), @lab{51}the man of Mari, with the mind of a beast, will not exercise sovereignty there! @lab{52 - 53}Now Enlil has mustered the Tidnumite(s) in (the land of) Amurrum as my helper(s). @lab{54 - 55}... @lab{56}The Elamite (forces) will be repulsed, @lab{52}Išbi-Erra will be captured, and @lab{58}the homeland will be restored (to me). @lab{59}The foreign land(s) will learn of my strength! @lab{60}From now on you .... @lab{61}It is urgent, you must make sure that everyone must not neglect (my orders)!
